node.title: Woman dies in water-related incident at Waikanae Beach, KƒÅpiti
node.description: It marks the fifth water-related death in the Wellington region this week.
node.content: ["A woman has died following a water-related incident at Waikanae Beach in K\u0101piti.", "The incident was reported to emergency services at around 1:30pm on Boxing Day, a police spokesperson said in a statement.\u00a0", "\"Police are making enquiries in relation to the death on behalf of the coroner,\" they said.", "The spokesperson did not elaborate on the circumstances of the incident.\u00a0", "Situated just north of Paraparaumu in the Wellington region, Waikanae Beach is a popular holiday destination during the summer months.\u00a0", "The incident marks the fifth water-related death in the region this week.", "On Christmas Eve, a man died in a diving-related death at Cape Palliser, a promontory on the Wairarapa coastline.\u00a0", "On Thursday, a 47-year-old man's body was recovered from Wellington Harbour on the capital's waterfront.", "Also on Thursday, a man's body was retrieved from under the Days Bay wharf. As reported by Stuff,\u00a0authorities were called to Days Bay at 10:45am and confirmed the Westpac Rescue helicopter, the dive squad and the police maritime unit had been searching for the missing man.", "On Tuesday evening, the body of kayaker Jack Skellett, 23, was found in Wellington Harbour. He was formally identified by police on Thursday morning."]
